## A. 

First, let us determine the new market value of the company by multiplying the shares by their respective share prices. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{New market value}
&={\text{(375,000 $\times$ \$67.00) + (50,000 $\times$ \$58.00)}}\\[5pt]
&={\text{\$25,125,000.00 + \$2,900,000.00}}\\[5pt]
&={\textbf{\$28,025,000.00}}
\end{aligned}$$ 

**The new market value of the company amounts to $28,025,000.00.**
